<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1905-11-03T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1905-11-03T00:00:00-05:00" n="809" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d809">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Eddy</persName> to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">St.
                                        Petersburg</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1905-11-03"><hi rend="italic">November 3,
                                1905</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>(Mr. Eddy reports that no disturbances have taken place in this city
                            during the last twenty-four hours. The disturbances are apparently over,
                            and it is believed that the railways will be put in operation early next
                            week.)</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>